hinduism on bali is unique because it is woven into and around the original balinese animistic religion. the two now have become one for the balinese - a true sign of tolerance and acceptance. nyepi dates: 5 march 2011 (caka year 1933) 23rd march 2012 (caka year 1934) - probable ogoh-ogoh procession on the eve of nyepi there are an estimated 20,000 temples (pura) on the island, each of which holds festivals (odalan) at least twice yearly. with many other auspicious days throughout the year there are always festivities going on. the large island-wide festivals are determined by two local 